Durban - Two men have been arrested for the murders of six people at a shopping centre in Vulindlela in Empangeni at the weekend. The men, aged 32 and 39 were charged with murder and expected to appear in court in due course. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, police spokesperson said that on Friday, a group of heavily armed men entered the shopping complex in KwaDlangezwa near Empangeni and opened fire on guards and others at the facility. Five people died at the scene and a sixth person died in hospital a few days later. “The men fled with an undisclosed amount of money. Among the victims who died are two security guards who were performing guard duties at the complex and an innocent bystander who was sitting in his vehicle. The supermarket owners were not injured during the robbery,” he said. The men faces charges of murder, attempted murder and robbery were opened at Mthunzini police station for further investigation. Daily News